about: Fine Casual Dining by The Lombok Lodge Hospitality . FLAVORS Restaurant, nestled within the charming confines of 'The Lombok Lodge, Boutique Hotel, Medana Bay, presents a delightful and unique Fine Casual Dining Experience. . With Chef Jiwa Raga's exceptional Cuisine and the restaurant's unique Wine List, your visit to FLAVORS is an absolute must during your stay in Lombok! . FLAVORS Restaurant is ideally located on the northwestern coast of Lombok, a mere 35-minute drive from Senggigi area. Just 15 minutes away from the enchanting Gili Islands and a short 5 minutes walk from the 'The Oberoi' Hotel. Enjoy the captivating scene as local fishermen ply their craf, casting their nets into the shimmering ocean under the moonlit night sky, in pursuit of the ocean's bounty. . name: Pinksunset Kiss Gili T
about: Welcome to PinkSunset Kiss at Gili Trawangan! Located on the island’s most iconic sunset spot, PinkSunset Kiss offers breathtaking views of the Lombok Strait and the majestic Bali volcano all at once. Join us every day for live DJ sessions, mesmerizing fire dance shows, soulful saxophone performances — and soon, thrilling live drum sets — as the sun dips below the horizon. Pizza lovers, get ready to indulge: our talented Italian chef, Riccardo from Rome, crafts some of the most delicious, authentic pizzas you’ll ever taste. Come relax, dance, and connect with friends — old and new — in the vibrant and welcoming atmosphere of PinkSunset Kiss. Every visit promises unforgettable moments set against the spectacular natural beauty of Gili Trawangan. See you soon at PinkSunset Kiss – where every sunset is a celebration!

Our menu is focused on fresh, healthy and healing foods - all super delicious and predominantly plant based. about: This unconventional "Locanda" is born one year ago in full pandemic time, As a Chef like many other colleagues I was without a job isolated in Gili Trawangan. I decided so to start cook some food for sell it online. Helped with my sweet wife Tania we were cooking and delivering on all Gili Trawangan. The name My House is because we actually live here and after seeing the good respond of our customers on delivery we decided also to use the backyard of my house for make a small place to eat. We love to keep this atmosphere of traditional "Locanda" The menu is on WhatsApp catalog and change based on available ingredients. We buy ours ingredients from lokal farms, fisherman and butcher for help also the local economy.

name: TERRA - Plant Based Food
about: Terra restaurant serves innovative, inspiring and 100% plant based food in the heart of Kuta Lombok. All food is vegan & gluten free. A place indeed where you can nourish your body, mind and soul, and learn through a new culinary experience. Our kitchen is run by passionate Japanese Chef Mamiko Eda, an Ashtanga Yoga lover, with over 10 years experience in vegan and cooked food. The venue will be divided into three different atmospheres. On the first floor, with the street entrance, we will find the takeaway section or healing station; where it will be served breakfast, juices and healthy drinks, as well as a buffet of salads and cakes. The restaurant will be located on the top floor with an indoor and outdoor area. On the same level, we will find the AC lounge area for reading and work, with sofas and bookshelves full of books about nutrition, health, yoga and other subjects. The lounge will be a comfortable sitting area and the cosy corner of the venue.

name: Markisa Restaurant
about: Sun is an ingredient at Markisa, the Indonesian word for passion fruit. We thought it only fitting to name our restaurant after the fruit that takes centre stage in the design of the restaurant and hotel. Markisa finds its roots in honest Mediterranean cooking, with a bit of an Italian bias. We will be working closely with local organic farmers and fishermen and believe strongly in respecting the integrity of our ingredients. We strive to produce as much yummy goodness in house, in a way nona would be proud of. From slow ferment naturally leavened breads to preserving peppers, hand rolling pasta and curing sardines. We Love food, like really love it, and hope that you can taste it in our cooking.

name: Omah Cobek Restaurant
about: Starting from our love of the traditional cuisine of Java (especially Yogyakarta) hard we encountered on the island of Lombok that time, and we see the lack of diversity of culinary in Mataram (2008), then with a capital of family recipes, we want to share the experience of taste to be enjoyed by foodies on the island of Lombok. Also based on the survey, the food is very spicy flavor arouse your appetite Indonesian society, especially the island of Lombok. True to its name "York" which means "chili" in Javanese, the island of Lombok has chili is more spicy than other regions in Indonesia, we are determined to present a traditional Indonesian dishes are made from chili (chili) as for the name we chose was omah mortar. Omah in the Java language means house, while cobek is a tool to smooth spice and often used to make the sauce, so it is "Omah cobek" is the home of a mortar which means lots of available-chili sauce. Based on the name, Omah cobek is a restaurant with the peculiarities of various kinds of sauce appetizing. Finally, with determination and courage and invoke the aid of the Lord Almighty we opened our first outlet in Jl.Maktal 6 Mataram on January 11, 2009.

name: Lumbung Restaurant
about:
The award winning Lumbung Restaurant at The Oberoi, Lombok takes its name from the traditional rice storage containers that are integral to daily life on Lombok.
Located within the lush hotel gardens, Lumbung Restaurant includes an open sided, thatched structure and an al fresco courtyard. Once a week, guests are entertained by traditional Balinese dancers and musicians performing in the adjacent amphitheatre.
The menu features Indonesian, Western and Indian cuisine, topped off with delicious imported cheese, homemade ice creams and sorbets. We also offer a range of sugar free desserts and a special Children's menu. 
Lumbung Restaurant also hosts special dining nights. Please contact +62 370 6138 444 for reservation.

name: Le Bistro
about:
Closed until March 2019 for Renovation

Le Bistro is a french fusion food restaurant located on the beach, facing the mount Rinjani. Owned by french friends, the head chef is also French. We get our inspiration from various countries and accomodate them with the local style. We are specialized in fresh raw tuna. The Tuna Tartare, Tuna Ceviche and Tuna Tataki are our signature dishes. We also propose grilled fish fillet, meats, burgers, and a wide range of imported wine. We use only fresh ingredients and we rinse the vegetables with drinkable water, so you can go for salads as well. All the breads we use for our sandwiches and burgers are home-made We have great barmen to do good cocktails and last but not least, awesome chocolate brownies and gelato to finish your meal. All the team will do his best to host you and provide you the best possible service, but please, don't forget that you are on holidays, on a small remote island with a different culture and education, and a different relation to the time. Enjoy that ;)

name: Cafe Rinjani Dawn
about: Cafe Rinjani Dawn is a cozy, informal restaurant located at the start of the Senaru Waterfall Trail. Known for its authentic Indonesian cuisine and locally sourced coffee, the cafe offers stunning views of rice terraces stretching down to a distant ocean. Whether you’re enjoying traditional dishes, a freshly made pizza, or just relaxing with a cup of coffee, Cafe Rinjani Dawn provides a welcoming atmosphere for all. Popular in the evenings, it's the perfect spot to unwind with an ice-cold beer or a cool glass of wine after a day of exploring Lombok. As part of the Rinjani Dawn Adventures family, we’re committed to supporting the local community through our Sasak Warriors initiative. By dining with us, you’re contributing to efforts that provide food aid, support education, and promote sustainability in Senaru. Whether you're fueling up before a trek or enjoying a laid-back evening, Cafe Rinjani Dawn is the perfect spot to enhance your Lombok adventure.

name: Curfew Restaurant And Beer Garden
about: Looking for some great craft beer, exceptional food, or just a place to kick back and relax? We've got you covered. We're proud to offer a fantastic selection of local craft beers that are all brewed right here in Indonesia. From hoppy IPA's to smooth lagers, we've got something on tap for everyone. If cocktails are more your thing, don't sweat it, we've got plenty to choose from. Our menu features a huge variety of locally sourced goods, from the highest quality produce to fresh fish caught daily. We work hard with our team of chefs and farmers to ensure that every dish we serve is thoughtfully prepared with the best ingredients available. Our commitment to sustainably and locally sourced food has given us the opportunity to explore the best that Lombok has to offer and support our local community. Right in the heart of Kuta, Lombok, Curfew is the perfect place to unwind and enjoy excellent food and drinks.

name: Serene Sunset
about: SERENE SUNSET BEACH is located on the beautiful sunset-side of the island, perfect for relaxing beach days and beautiful sunsets! Our big passion is to take care of our Environment, Mother Nature. This is way we banned Plastic and Cans totally from our Menu! We offer you always fresh ingredients and always made with lots of love! On the Menu you find our famous, refreshing Mojito's, fresh Organic Juices, tropical Fruits and of course not to forget our homemade Pizza and Pasta! SERENE SUNSET is our home which we work hard with our hearts to make it as enjoyable and comfortable as possible - and we love to share our little piece of heaven with you! Feel Home and safe with us, if you have any special request or concern, there will always be someone to help you! Again, we are on a little tiny Island in the middle of nowhere with limited access to actually everything, so lets just chill, relax and appreciate life more together:) We're looking forward to have you in Serene Sunset!

name: Sunrise Beach Club
about: Fusion Style Reflecting our guests from all over the world, the Sunrise Beach Club menu offers Fusion style modern dishes, Tapas and Indonesian Specialities all day long; with a hard to beat BBQ at nighttime. A dedicated kids menu makes sure our little guests are also taken care of. Selected Wine For those who love their wines, we offer selected good quality French and Italian wines at reasonable prices, something hard to find on Gili Air. For Champagne lovers we offer Jean Pierre Brut, Lanson and Bollinger. 75m Beach Front With 75 meters direct beach front Sunrise Beach Club has 2 main beach seating areas. The wooden sundeck invites for both lounging and eating directly above the sand with direct sea views and open skies. Diversity The Beach Club offers various seating areas for different tastes with one menu throughout. You can also watch the gentle turquoise waves from our covered beach restaurant area, which is decked out with white washed rattan furniture.

name: Bahia Restaurant & Beachbar - Gili Air
about: Bahia is a beachfront restaurant and bar on Gili Air, offering island-fusion cuisine, tropical cocktails and a relaxed atmosphere right on the sand. Guests can choose from sunbeds, lounge chairs, shaded tables, comfy couches or indoor seating. Our menu highlights fresh, colorful dishes made with quality ingredients ideal for sharing or enjoying on your own. Whether you stop by for a swim or snorkel just in front, come for a long lazy lunch, or unwind with cocktails at sunset, Bahia brings together friendly service, comfort, and a beautiful oceanfront setting that makes every visit memorable.

name: Flowers & Fire Wholefoods Cafe
about: Situated under a sprawling sapodilla tree and our Flowers & Fire Yoga Garden, our open air plant based cafe serves simple but delicious whole food creations with plenty of fresh, minimally processed and enzyme rich ingredients. Everything, from our bread, to our peanut butter, to our dressings and sauces are made from scratch using healthy and whole ingredients. We cater to vegetarian and vegan diets, offering meals that are satisfying, artfully crafted and will leave you feeling balanced. Our food philosophy is that simple, hearty, fresh, healthy, digestible and delicious food is best. But there is always space for good coffee and an extensive tea selection. And wait until you try our homemade “I can’t believe it’s not Ben & Jerry’s” raw vegan, creamy fresh fruit ice cream, served with a crackly cacoa topping and sliced sapodilla from our tree. Not only will our inviting cafe nourish you, but we also offer poolside community wifi facilities for digital nomads visiting Gili Air.

name: Zorba The Greek
about: Zorba the Greek / Go Veggies Go Vegan is the only one restaurant plant based joint and mediteranian cuisine in Lombok. We used to think that plant-based diet is impossible, compelled by our love and respect for mother earth as well as a desire for a healthier lifestyle we decided to do something radical, we have never look back. We’re committed to making most amazing burgers and vegan food in Lombok. We break the stereotype of burgers, sandwiches, vegan food. In short, we rock with plant-based burgers, sandwiches, soups and delicious vegan food and more. name: Restaurant Codium
about: Codium is a beachside restaurant in Lombok, located near the shores of Kuta. We serve Mediterranean-inspired dishes alongside fresh Indonesian flavors, with a special focus on local seaweed, seafood, and seasonal vegetables. Whether you’re looking for a relaxed restaurant by the beach in Lombok or a unique dining experience with ocean views, we are the place to be! Our open-fire kitchen showcases the island’s finest ingredients — with a special focus on amazing locally line-caught seafood — prepared simply and beautifully in a style inspired by the Mediterranean. Relax with your feet in the sand, enjoying Sunset, while our chefs cook over the flames, pairing each dish with a thoughtful selection of wines and crafted cocktails. Soft light, ocean breeze, and soulful flavors create a warm, intimate atmosphere that makes every dinner at Codium memorable.

name: SANDS Beach Club Gili Air
about: SANDS Beach Club & Restaurant is an all-day hangout and beachfront dining spot on Gili Air, designed to follow the relaxed rhythm of island life. Start your day with freshly baked pastries, sourdough bread, and quality coffee from our in-house bakery. Spend the afternoon by the pool or on the beach enjoying light lunches, fresh dishes, and refreshing drinks. As the sun sets, SANDS transforms into a relaxed yet vibrant dinner spot with handcrafted cocktails and a menu featuring fresh seafood, high quality steak, pizza, sushi and island-inspired mains. Welcoming families, couples, solo travellers, and locals alike, SANDS offers a laid-back atmosphere without any pressure... just good food, great drinks, and beautiful ocean views from morning to night. Whether you’re stopping by for breakfast, spending the day by the pool, or joining us for sunset cocktails and dinner, SANDS is the perfect place to experience all-day living on Gili Air.

about: Captikus is a hidden speak easy bar located behind an old Chinese-Indonesian pharmacy. "Toko Obat" in Indonesia. The bar transports you back in time and takes great pride in their Indonesian inspired cocktail menu. Indonesia is also called “The Mother of Spices” and these distinctive spices can be found back in multiple cocktails throughout the menu. Captikus does not only focusses on Indonesian flavours but also dedicate a big part of their menu for “Classics” and “Modern Classics”. A Hidden Gem in Kuta Lombok Step into Captikus, where the vibrant spirit of Indonesia meets the elegance of a speakeasy. Tucked away in Kuta Lombok, our bar offers an enchanting escape, blending the rich flavors of local ingredients with the timeless allure of classic cocktails.
